## List of certificates

> Headers

```
Content-type: application/json
```

> Request example

```shell
curl https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/certificates?shop_id=...&shop_secret=...&code=...&date_from=...&date_to=...
```

> The above command returns JSON structured like this:

```json
{
  "status": "success",
  "payload": [
    {
      "id": 333,
      "status": "created",
      "code": "abc---asdsaf3-...",
      "nominal": 5000,
      "balance": 3980,
      "owner_identifier": "...",
      "owner_name": "...",
      "buyer_identifier": "...",
      "created_date": "...",
      "activated_date": "...",
      "expiration_date": "...",
      "batch": null,
      "pool": {
        "id": 17,
        "status": "active",
        "flexible_nominal": 6000,
        "personal": true,
        "expiration_days": 30,
        "min_order_value": 1000,
        "payable_order_share": 70,
        "exclude_products": [{... }, {... }, ...]
      }
    },
    ...
  ]
}
```

Returns list of pool's certificates filtered by date of provided event.

### HTTP Request


`GET https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/certificates`

### Query Parameters

| Parameter   | Required | Description                                              |
|-------------|----------|----------------------------------------------------------|
| shop_id     | true     | Your API key                                             |
| shop_secret | true     | Your API secret key                                      |
| code        | true     | Certificate pool code                                    |
| event       | true     | Certificate state event: created, activated, deactivated |
| date_from   | true     | Start of period (YYYY-MM-DD)                             |
| date_to     | true     | End of period (YYYY-MM-DD)                               |

Filter by period depends on provided state:

- for `created` it will filter by created date;
- for `activated` it will filter by activation date;
- for `deactivated` it will filter by deactivation date.



